I had such high hopes after this place was recommended to me by a vegetarian friend. I am only giving this place two stars for the milkshakes. The food and service ranged from mediocre at best to terrible at worst.  My initial impressions upon walking in the door were positive: I liked the diner ambiance, with cracked and fading hipster-friendly vinyl couches featuring 80s pop-icons (with a Hawaiian flavor). The soundtrack playing could have come off of my iTunes playlist, but was a little loud and made conversation difficult. There was apparently only one guy serving two customers at the bar and we seated ourselves. More than a few minutes later, we learned that the other two "customers" were actually waitstaff when one of them finally came by with menus. It took the other one another ten minutes to come back and ask for our order.  When the food finally arrived it was as disappointing as the service. The burger I ordered was pedestrian at best. It was serviceable, but not worth what they charged. You could do similar with a frozen patty and some hamburger buns from the grocery store. The homemade ginger ale was poorly mixed - the flavor syrup was trapped below the ice and not mixed with the tonic. This does not speak well for cocktails at a place that also works as a bar and lounge. My companion's breakfast burrito oozed a orange grease, and continued to bleed this sludge throughout our meal. Biting into it did not improve the flavour, and while I appreciated their efforts at including taco chips to give it a bit of crunch and texture, they were overwhelmed and saturated by the thick oil. My companion wishes I'd photographed the dying beast to document how truly unappetizing it was.  The one bright spot was their vegetarian milkshake, using a coconut base instead of milk. It truly was a great milkshake, and if the rest of the food had been comparable, this would have been a four or five star joint.  I guess vegetarians don't have a lot of options for dining out?

I've heard good things about Downbeat as a place to eat, unfortunately my experience tonight was not the case. Sad to say the service to night was subpar. Our server only checked on us once in about 20 minutes. I also had to flag down the server for more water.  The worst part of my visit was the main reason I went, the food. In the picture I posted, you can see an overcooked tortilla that was used for my BBQ wrap that immediately unwrapped once I picked it up (due to the burnt/stiff tortilla). You can also see burnt tortilla chips that made up the majority of nachos that were ordered. Considering quality for the price point; rip off.  The only saving grace was their bartender's expertly crafted cocktails, I would have ordered more drinks but our server didn't visit us much 🤷‍♂️
